   "https://reference.wolfram.com/language/tutorial/Evaluation.html"],
 " provides more information on the standard evaluation sequence and \
nonstandard argument evaluation."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"902078a8-c4f1-48d4-aedd-909225174223"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Attributes: Orderless, Listable and Flat", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0d169e66-89f8-4f5d-aa90-527bf1b868d8"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Head[elem1, elem2, elem3, ...]",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Program",ExpressionUUID->"1f12e928-2f57-41e2-8704-\
59bcf2739b5e"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Evaluate the head of the expression.",
 FontWeight->"Plain"]], "ItemNumbered",
 FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"3632eac6-e938-4856-9343-c418961b090c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Evaluate elements.", "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"a6de47f3-b60c-4754-8d8e-90f3756fd87f"],

Cell["\<\
Standard Evaluation Procedure: Evaluate all the elements in turn.\
\>", "SubitemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"4f624932-50e1-4809-b13a-26ccc30ce169"],

Cell["\<\
Nonstandard Evaluation Procedure: Evaluate selected elements in turn, or do \
not evaluate any element.\
\>", "SubitemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"795e17a6-2258-4a27-9c0f-99a52a3e174a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Apply transformations associated with the attributes \
Orderless, Listable and Flat.",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"2da4f6c9-c697-495d-\
a550-47959f4f0895"],

Cell["Apply any definitions that you have given.", "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"c11f80af-c717-495e-81a7-d3ded3851070"],

Cell["Apply any built-in definitions.", "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"bfa57289-d29a-452b-8e07-bf9545b2b3c4"],

Cell["Evaluate the result.", "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"8cdedd07-764a-4174-9ca4-a198a878c40d"],

Cell["\<\
HoldFirst, HoldRest and HoldAll are responsible for instantiating the \
nonstandard evaluation procedure in Step 2 of the evaluation loop, but they \
are not the only attributes that a function can have in Wolfram Language. The \
attributes Orderless, Listable and Flat carry with them transformation rules \
that comprise Step 3 of the loop.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d0e258df-c064-4bf4-93f0-1840a07e7175"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Orderless", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"d9d3e11c-81be-47c8-b391-20bed8b7a234"],

Cell["\<\
Orderless indicates that elements should automatically be sorted into \
canonical order. It corresponds to the mathematical property of commutativity:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a8ec53fb-577e-4ccf-9649-0427a13e4a04"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "f", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"f", "[", 
   RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"x", "^", "y"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[81]:=",ExpressionUUID->"2576abfe-9d19-4714-8d92-a14d554f7b53"],

